How do you know it is not a driver issue? It may be a bug that only shows with Classic Shell. It is possible some rare condition that Classic Shell is causing is not handled well by the driver. To the best of my knowledge I am doing things correctly. I am using a pretty high-level API, and it is pretty hard to misuse it.<br />You can try different skins. In particular try one with no transparency, like Classic.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2">Ivo</a> — Mon Jul 22, 2013 8:24 am</p><hr />
